The paper focuses on the feasibility study of RGB-D SLAM for indoor robot navigation, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. However, the paper extensively evaluates ORBSLAM2, a visual SLAM method, and introduces a new large and diverse HomeRobot dataset, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The statistical analysis of the results and finding correlations between the metrics and the attributes of the trajectories also involve machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on indoor robot navigation and evaluating the robustness of SLAM methods also involves the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
